Package ca.ualberta.cs.scandaloutraveltracker

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ViewInterface
    Part of MVC; all the views need to implement this interface if it needs to interact with any of the models.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Approver
    This is the Approver class which represents a user that has the capabilities of a Approver.
    BuildConfig  
    Claim
    Class that contains the Claim model.
    Claimant
    This is the Claimant class which represents a user that has the capabilities of a Claimant.
    ClaimApplication
    Helps setup the application for when the app is launched.
    ClaimController
    The Claim Controller class is used for making changes to a Claim that is supplied to the controller.
    ClaimList
    Class is a list that holds Claims.
    ClaimListActivity
    This activity is the first activity that is displayed to the user.
    ClaimListAdapter
    The ClaimListAdapter allows essential information from a Claim to be displayed in a ListView.
    ClaimListController
    When making edits to the Claim List model it should be done through this ClaimListController class.
    ClaimListMapper
    ClaimListMapper loads all the claims in the list using ClaimMapper.
    ClaimMapper
    The ClaimMapper helps us save all the data related to a claim.
    Constants
    Class contains all the values that are constant throughout the application.
    DatePickerFragment
    Creates a DatePicker dialog.
    Destination
    Class contains all the information that a Destination needs.
    DestinationListAdapter
    Allows essential information from the Destination class to be displayed in a ListView.
    EditClaimActivity
    This activity contains a claim that was selected from the ClaimListActivity and allows you to edit the claim.
    EditExpenseActivity
    Activity takes an expense from the ExpenseListActivity and allows the user to edit information about the expense.
    Expense
    Class that contains the Expense model.
    ExpenseController
    When supplied with an expense the controller allows you to edit expense information (expense should not be edited directly).
    ExpenseListActivity
    This activity displays the list of expenses that is related to the current claim.
    ExpenseListAdapter
    An adapter that allows an expense to display its essential information in a ListView.
    NewClaimActivity
    Activity that allows the user to add a new claim to the claim list.
    NewExpenseActivity
    This is the activity that provides functionality for adding a new expense to the current claim.

    User
